1
00:00:02,980 --> 00:00:04,620
Ariyom tatsat, to everyone.

2
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:07,300
My name is Sachidananda.

3
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:15,800
I recognize many of you and I'm happy to
see you so soon.

4
00:00:20,040 --> 00:00:23,660
And for those who I'm meeting for the
first time, thank you for your interest

5
00:00:23,660 --> 00:00:26,220
and support in the Yoga Vidya.

6
00:00:34,580 --> 00:00:43,780
The first talk in Uruguay during this
visit was yesterday evening.

7
00:00:44,360 --> 00:00:48,460
And the points that I forgot to mention,
I want to start with right now before we

8
00:00:48,460 --> 00:00:49,980
formally begin the session.

9
00:00:55,780 --> 00:00:58,780
One of those is thank you, Clara,
for translating.

10
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:06,740
So, as Janardhan mentioned, there are a
number of activities starting from

11
00:01:06,740 --> 00:01:07,040
tomorrow.

12
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:17,380
And I happen to be one of the
facilitators, but trust me when I say I'm

13
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:19,160
not trying to promote myself.

14
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:33,080
The topic of koshas and yogic bodies and
holistic health requires immersion.

15
00:01:41,380 --> 00:01:46,460
I've studied this for over 20 years,
but life changes have only happened in the

16
00:01:46,460 --> 00:01:47,160
past five.

17
00:02:01,740 --> 00:02:09,820
Because that's when I really had to apply
the theory.

18
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:15,580
So, you have an opportunity with the
activities planned to put yourself in an

19
00:02:15,580 --> 00:02:18,020
immersive yogic setting, routine.

20
00:02:26,340 --> 00:02:33,540
There are a few things I've identified
that really bring us into contact with all

21
00:02:33,540 --> 00:02:36,840
five koshas.

22
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,440
Five layers of what it means to be human.

23
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:50,640
One of those is pilgrimages.

24
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:59,840
And all cultures have that, to go on.

25
00:03:00,460 --> 00:03:05,260
Another is ashram life or monastery life,
monastic life.

26
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:11,180
Maybe you have access to that in Uruguay.

27
00:03:11,180 --> 00:03:23,380
A third is an anushtan or an extended
period of austerity.

28
00:03:28,060 --> 00:03:30,500
This is what shivaratri is traditionally.

29
00:03:33,140 --> 00:03:38,220
Some people don't eat for 24 hours.

30
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:42,220
I know people who don't drink a drop of
water for 24 hours.

31
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:51,240
I know people who will not swallow their
sweat, their spit, for 24 hours.

32
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:53,860
They'll spit it out rather than down their
throat.

33
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:04,080
Some people choose not to sleep for 24
hours.

34
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:12,680
Some people choose not to speak except the
name of God for 24 hours.

35
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:22,420
Some people will not speak at all and will
only repeat a mantra or nothing at all for

36
00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:23,340
24 hours.

37
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:34,060
And then, the fourth activity is a
curation.

38
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:35,200
An iterated retreat.

39
00:04:39,740 --> 00:04:45,840
Where it's designed to systematically help
us reflect on each of these layers of

40
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:46,200
being.

41
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:58,120
So if you're not planning any austerity or
pilgrimages in the next week,

42
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:12,620
I invite you to at least attend shivaratri
or any day or the whole retreat.

43
00:05:18,420 --> 00:05:20,000
And I mean that sincerely.

44
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:28,540
We can wait for life to bring us to our
knees and then figure out a survival plan.

45
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:41,080
Or we can willingly put ourselves into a
setting that deeply challenges us.

46
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:51,500
And recognize our strengths and weaknesses
in a context of positivity.

47
00:05:56,420 --> 00:06:01,640
I have slowly learned to prefer the latter
and I invite you to the same.

48
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:10,640
So that's about the activities.

49
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:16,600
And a few more disclaimers from my side.

50
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:25,780
I love talking about physical well-being.

51
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:28,720
Mental health.

52
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:32,680
Consciousness and the spirit.

53
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:37,660
But I'm not a physical trainer or a
doctor.

54
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:47,480
I'm not a certified therapist or
counselor.

55
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:50,620
And I'm not many other things.

56
00:06:52,700 --> 00:07:01,580
But I have dived into life and it has
pushed back against me numerous times.

57
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:16,100
And from those experiences I really like
to share what I've learned.

58
00:07:16,340 --> 00:07:22,400
Not to talk about what works but to
motivate you to really experiment with

59
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,040
your life in a holistic way.

60
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:35,760
There are multiple experts in this room.

61
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:40,180
My guess is no one of them can solve a
problem that you have.

62
00:07:44,940 --> 00:07:49,660
We have to learn to be able to read
ourselves at multiple layers.

63
00:07:49,660 --> 00:07:59,560
So whatever I say is just a hint,
please put it through your common sense

64
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,320
filters.

65
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:10,240
If it doesn't resonate, let it go.

66
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,460
Don't even hold on to it for a moment.

67
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:23,500
And if something does resonate,
note it down mentally or on paper and find

68
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:30,440
a way to unpack it.

69
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:42,380
Almost 90% of the talk is taken from my
training in the Satyananda Yoga tradition.

70
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:54,560
And I pay my deepest respects to the gurus
of that tradition, Swami Niranjan who is

71
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:57,000
living and Swami Satyananda who has left.

72
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:15,080
But I'm not an official representative of
the ashram or that branch of yoga.

73
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:18,740
I'm an okay practitioner getting better.

74
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:29,060
Last thing because I know it might affect
me at some point.

75
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:34,420
There is something about Uruguay and the
heart energy.

76
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:36,140
It just opens it up for me.

77
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:37,280
It makes me sensitive.

78
00:09:44,820 --> 00:09:50,180
So I already see some people tearing up
and that's going to get me super soft.

79
00:09:50,180 --> 00:10:00,520
So if I need to take a breath or two,
y'all just feel free to do the same at

80
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:01,080
that time.

81
00:10:06,740 --> 00:10:08,760
Any questions before we begin?

82
00:10:11,060 --> 00:10:17,460
Thank you very much for those of you who
had time to fill out the feedback form.

83
00:10:22,540 --> 00:10:28,880
It looks like for many of you the topic of
tonight is relatively new.

84
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:41,880
And a number of you are interested in
tools for self-reflection and life

85
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:42,340
harmony.

86
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:53,500
And for those of you who pointed out other
interests, I'm confident that there will

87
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:57,900
be something for each and every one of you
here tonight.

88
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:07,180
During one portion of the session we will
be lying down for yoga nidra.

89
00:11:11,260 --> 00:11:16,940
But until that point, please arrange
yourself comfortably where you can see

90
00:11:16,940 --> 00:11:20,140
without stressing your neck.

91
00:11:26,660 --> 00:11:29,720
And then for the practice itself we can
come back to our mats.

92
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:41,530
We'll go ahead and begin with Shantipat.

93
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:48,560
Please bring yourself into a comfortable
sitting asana.

94
00:11:52,540 --> 00:12:03,420
Any position where you can sit comfortably
still for about five minutes.

95
00:12:04,210 --> 00:12:08,240
And ideally where the spine is also
comfortably upright.

96
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:18,460
Begin to make any physical adjustments you
need to bring balance to the left and

97
00:12:18,460 --> 00:12:20,620
right half of the physical body.

98
00:12:20,620 --> 00:12:34,720
Using the contact points between the body
and the floor as feedback into that

99
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:35,280
symmetry.

100
00:12:50,300 --> 00:13:00,560
Once you create a stable base,
bring the awareness into the sit bones and

101
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:04,460
the buttocks and feel the weight
distribution on each side.

102
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:18,800
And then move the awareness up the torso
from base to top of shoulders.

103
00:13:27,020 --> 00:13:32,380
Feeling for symmetry and balance in this
mid portion of the body.

104
00:13:41,820 --> 00:13:50,840
Notice if there is any tension in the
shoulders or around the neck.

105
00:13:53,020 --> 00:13:57,980
And see if you can suggest or allow
yourself to relax any amount.

106
00:13:57,980 --> 00:14:08,780
The hands in a mudra.

107
00:14:09,380 --> 00:14:14,180
A simple one is to touch thumb tip to the
index finger.

108
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:22,260
Palms up or down.

109
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:27,960
Bring the awareness into the neck and feel
that it's balanced.

110
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:34,020
Bring your attention to your neck and feel
that it's aligned with your shoulders.

111
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:42,020
Creating a natural length to the lower
spine.

112
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:46,920
And that the head is floating effortlessly
on the neck.

113
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,520
Eyes and mouth gently closed.

114
00:14:58,860 --> 00:15:03,760
Feel into your whole sitting position as
you visualize yourself in your mind.

115
00:15:26,990 --> 00:15:32,890
It's possible that impressions from the
day are moving within you.

116
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:42,310
How are you experiencing that?

117
00:15:45,730 --> 00:15:49,030
Is it at the physical level somewhere in
the body?

118
00:15:56,190 --> 00:16:00,230
Is it revealed in the way that you're
breathing right now?

119
00:16:06,570 --> 00:16:10,510
Or maybe thoughts or memories moving
through the mind.

120
00:16:16,410 --> 00:16:20,190
Or emotions or feelings still being
carried.

121
00:16:27,870 --> 00:16:32,690
However the proof of your life is present
within you, be a witness to it.

122
00:16:40,230 --> 00:16:45,390
Permit yourself to be that witness,
step back and just observe.

123
00:16:58,290 --> 00:17:02,650
Connecting with your own breath,
begin to deepen it both directions.

124
00:17:08,130 --> 00:17:13,670
So that over a number of breaths,
you're exhaling more completely and

125
00:17:13,670 --> 00:17:15,290
inhaling more deeply.

126
00:17:35,890 --> 00:17:43,610
Add to this deepening breath a mental
focus.

127
00:17:43,610 --> 00:17:45,770
The frontal psychic passage.

128
00:17:49,070 --> 00:17:55,410
An imaginary line, pathway or tube running
along the front of the torso.

129
00:18:02,670 --> 00:18:09,730
It starts at the navel, moves straight up
through the sternum and ends at the throat

130
00:18:09,730 --> 00:18:10,070
pit.

131
00:18:13,610 --> 00:18:21,930
It starts at the navel, runs through the
sternum and terminates at the throat pit.

132
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:29,830
With the next breath in, guide breath and
awareness up this pathway.

133
00:18:35,130 --> 00:18:39,910
And with the exhalation, guide breath and
awareness back down to the navel.

134
00:18:46,910 --> 00:18:50,650
Continue this for a number of breaths.

135
00:19:06,780 --> 00:19:12,780
If you find that the mind is not willing
to travel in a straight line, do not force

136
00:19:12,780 --> 00:19:16,220
it.

137
00:19:26,050 --> 00:19:29,010
With each new breath, a fresh start.

138
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:46,700
On the next inhalation, as you move up the
torso, continue all the way to the eyebrow

139
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:47,300
center.

140
00:19:56,700 --> 00:20:02,680
Hold your focus at an imaginary point
between the two eyebrows, just above the

141
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:03,300
brow line.

142
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:15,940
Turn the eyes inwards, as if to look at
that point from inside.

143
00:20:22,140 --> 00:20:26,760
Imagine looking at a flame which burns
steady and bright.

144
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:39,300
If the image does not readily appear,
remember a favorite candle.

145
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:48,620
Or feel free to draw the outline of that
candle.

146
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:55,320
To see the colors of a flame.

147
00:20:57,880 --> 00:21:00,760
Or to feel a warmth at that point.

148
00:21:04,780 --> 00:21:08,840
With our awareness on this inner light,
we'll chant the mantra OM three times

149
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:09,460
together.

150
00:21:14,060 --> 00:21:17,680
Followed by the opening Shanti mantras all
together.

151
00:21:20,900 --> 00:21:26,500
If you're unfamiliar with any mantra,
simply listen and feel into the vibrations

152
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:27,760
around you.

153
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:38,180
Slow, full breath in to chant the mantra
OM.

154
00:21:57,200 --> 00:22:00,500
OM OM

155
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:41,380
Om Sahana Bhavatu Sahano Bhunaktu
Sahaveeryam Karavavahe Tejas

156
00:22:41,380 --> 00:22:56,340
Vinavaditamastu Ma Vindhisavahe Om Shanti
Shanti Shanti Hi

157
00:23:06,250 --> 00:23:12,190
Remain with your body still and eyes
closed for a few moments longer,

158
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:21,470
and consider the intention for which you
are here this evening.

159
00:23:29,980 --> 00:23:36,820
And if there is any aspect of your life
that you invite radical, positive

160
00:23:36,820 --> 00:23:38,600
transformation into,

161
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:53,700
how could you form a short, positive
sentence to describe the transformation

162
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:54,640
you want?

163
00:24:01,980 --> 00:24:07,720
In a way that is not dependent on external
circumstances to change,

164
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:17,340
but rather some inner quality to emerge,
develop, or evolve.

165
00:24:17,340 --> 00:24:32,790
Imagine that that quality does emerge and
manifest in your being.

166
00:24:37,530 --> 00:24:39,190
What would that feel like?

167
00:24:39,290 --> 00:24:40,350
What would that look like?

168
00:24:43,910 --> 00:24:49,230
How would you move through your day,
through your life with this new ability

169
00:24:49,230 --> 00:24:50,430
and transformation?

170
00:24:57,130 --> 00:25:03,070
Is this possibility imaginable,
or is it far from imaginable?

171
00:25:10,230 --> 00:25:15,990
Are you able to contact the new emotions
you would experience, or is that out of

172
00:25:15,990 --> 00:25:16,430
reach?

173
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:32,280
Bring your awareness to the heart center
between the sternum and the spine.

174
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:39,250
Take a few deep breaths in and out.

175
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:46,860
Imagine breathing into that point and
breathing out of that point.

176
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:56,220
And bring the hands together in
pranamudra, thumbs touching the sternum.

177
00:26:01,220 --> 00:26:09,980
Rubbing the hands vigorously, generating
as much heat as you can.

178
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:16,040
And when you have something to share back
to your eyes, cover the closed eyes with

179
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:20,720
those palms.

180
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:29,180
Noticing any colors or shapes,
or maybe simply void.

181
00:26:31,980 --> 00:26:35,340
And take a deep breath in through the eyes
into yourself.

182
00:26:39,520 --> 00:26:47,300
And exhaling, you can slowly lower the
hands, and open the eyes.

183
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:49,980
Hari Om Tat Sat

184
00:26:53,300 --> 00:26:56,780
Is that new to anyone, to do a Shantipat?

185
00:27:01,560 --> 00:27:02,400
No?

186
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:03,100
Yes?

187
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:03,820
Great!

188
00:27:05,780 --> 00:27:12,620
I believe that Swami Satyananda Saraswati
and the Satyananda Yoga tradition are...

189
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:21,240
are pure geniuses.

190
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:29,020
You take something that we do at the
beginning and end of every class,

191
00:27:34,020 --> 00:27:37,100
that for many of us we think of it as
routine,

192
00:27:41,180 --> 00:27:41,860
obligatory.

193
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:48,560
And yet, guides and teachers like him,

194
00:27:52,220 --> 00:27:55,500
and other masters I've had in other
modalities,

195
00:27:58,540 --> 00:28:03,140
have taught me that what you do the most
is probably the most significant.

196
00:28:07,180 --> 00:28:18,600
For students of the Satyananda Yoga
tradition, the things we tend to do the

197
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:21,540
most, chant the mantra Om,

198
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:28,860
Shantipat, and repetition of Sankalpa.

199
00:28:31,300 --> 00:28:36,180
A Shantipat is an entire package,
it's a sadhana.

200
00:28:40,840 --> 00:28:50,940
It asks us to bring awareness into our
physical body, to observe our energetic

201
00:28:50,940 --> 00:29:02,040
state, often reflected in our breath,
to be a witness of mental activity,

202
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:10,800
to be a witness of emotional presence or
feelings,

203
00:29:15,100 --> 00:29:19,820
and independent of whatever storm or calm
is within,

204
00:29:28,740 --> 00:29:35,080
to stabilize ourselves and complete a
process from beginning to end.

205
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:45,060
That is a sufficient life teaching,
we don't need much more yoga than that.

206
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:55,320
The issue is we have so many tools,
and very few of them are actually being

207
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:55,940
applied.

208
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:06,440
Think about any time today where you felt
stressed,

209
00:30:10,400 --> 00:30:21,880
or knocked off balance, having done
Shantipat a thousand times, did anyone

210
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:25,900
today set aside three minutes to go
through it to recover?

211
00:30:30,260 --> 00:30:33,720
Did anyone at a moment of imbalance

212
00:30:37,740 --> 00:30:41,100
think to do Shantipat to recover that
balance?

213
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:53,800
Because we ritualize these techniques,
rather than seeing them as the tools that

214
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:54,360
they are.

215
00:30:57,460 --> 00:31:01,600
I really don't want you to do with that
information that's going to come through

216
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:02,560
today.

217
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:13,940
Find ways to put the awareness into daily
life.

218
00:31:18,220 --> 00:31:21,280
And I'll try and suggest some ways we can
do that.

219
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:30,560
What was the title of this talk,
Ceci?

220
00:31:34,860 --> 00:31:35,940
Habitarte por completo, no?

221
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:37,120
Habitarte is...

222
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:40,440
To live in your body completely.

223
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:43,520
Ah, yes, to live fully within yourself.

224
00:31:46,180 --> 00:31:51,960
As a traveler, I am blessed to be staying
in many homes.

225
00:31:57,540 --> 00:32:00,580
And I have a very curious personality.

226
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:04,120
Some may say nosy.

227
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:08,420
Some may say snoopy.

228
00:32:08,420 --> 00:32:11,200
Some may say, I don't know how to say
snoopy.

229
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:13,200
How do you say snoopy, Nuria?

230
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:16,040
Chismoso, yes.

231
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:19,740
So yoga is well suited for me.

232
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:25,620
Because if someone says, ah, there's this
thing called the subconscious,

233
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:31,320
I want to know how to get inside it.

234
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:36,480
And if someone says, there's this thing
called the unconscious,

235
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:41,660
and I say, well, what is it?

