shanti, shanti.

984
01:59:02,230 --> 01:59:05,510
Take a slow, full breath in to chant the
mantra OM.

985
01:59:05,510 --> 01:59:07,470
Slowly inhale deeply.

986
01:59:57,120 --> 02:00:00,500
Shanti, shanti, shanti.

987
02:00:05,300 --> 02:00:06,820
Hari Om.

988
02:00:11,440 --> 02:00:13,640
Bring the hands into prana mudra.

989
02:00:16,040 --> 02:00:17,380
Around the palming.

990
02:00:20,300 --> 02:00:23,700
When you have warmth to share back to the
eyes, cover them.

991
02:00:29,460 --> 02:00:33,140
Take a moment to notice anything you might
see or not see.

992
02:00:36,420 --> 02:00:38,380
And take a deep breath into yourself.

993
02:00:42,400 --> 02:00:44,120
Exhaling, lowering the hands.

994
02:00:46,440 --> 02:00:47,460
Hari Om Tat Sat.

995
02:00:49,440 --> 02:00:52,560
Thank you for that extra bit of time.

996
02:00:52,560 --> 02:00:59,540
There are, at least, there's always extra
ideas to share.

997
02:00:59,760 --> 02:01:03,140
What can I say other than I need five days
to share them?

998
02:01:09,280 --> 02:01:13,880
A lot of these sharings are many years of
synthesis.

999
02:01:14,140 --> 02:01:20,240
So my gratitude to you for giving an
audience to organize these thoughts that

1000
02:01:20,240 --> 02:01:20,900
have been collected.

1001
02:01:28,400 --> 02:01:31,420
We did record it and I will happily share
those.

1002
02:01:31,520 --> 02:01:35,940
There will be a feedback form and at the
end of the form will be a link to it.

1003
02:01:36,100 --> 02:01:38,040
So you can listen again if you'd like to.

1004
02:01:49,440 --> 02:01:52,540
And finally, I really invite you to bring
your hands into prana mudra.

1005
02:01:52,540 --> 02:01:56,320
Bring awareness of your koshas into daily
life.

1006
02:02:00,840 --> 02:02:06,500
I think many things will come through this
framework when you begin to do that.

1007
02:02:12,300 --> 02:02:13,060
Hari Om Tat Sat.

1008
02:02:13,060 --> 02:02:14,740
Thank you.

1009
02:02:17,380 --> 02:02:19,980
It's 9.15 for those of you who need to
leave.

